{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01LTLpuckLoB49RgpsRNtrBp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The canary routing now works correctly.\n\n## Root cause\nThe `canary-canary` Ingress (host `canary.example.com`, backend `canary-echo`) had the canary trigger configured as:\n```\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always\n```\nWith an explicit `canary-by-header-value`, the `X-Canary` header must match that exact value to route to the canary backend. So `X-Canary: beta` did **not** match `always`, and all traffic fell through to the stable backend.\n\n(The other `canary-alt` Ingress is a decoy — different host `canary-alt.example.com`, labeled `benchmark.decoy: \"true\"`, and points at `stable-echo`.)\n\n## Fix\nChanged the annotation on `canary-canary` to match the required header value:\n```\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: beta\n```\nNo application Deployments or Services were touched — only the Ingress annotation.\n\n## Verification\n- No header → `stable` ✓\n- `X-Canary: beta` → `canary` ✓ (stable across 3 repeated runs)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":341,"cache_read_input_tokens":34762,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":341},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbc14d3b-849e-4554-b203-4815fabfe371","uuid":"cdaabf39-2917-4511-a09e-e00d6df570ad","request_id":"req_011CcASUbYJNpmcxN6QSxmjC"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":35337,"duration_api_ms":29175,"ttft_ms":1614,"ttft_stream_ms":1613,"time_to_request_ms":39,"num_turns":6,"result":"Done. The canary routing now works correctly.\n\n## Root cause\nThe `canary-canary` Ingress (host `canary.example.com`, backend `canary-echo`) had the canary trigger configured as:\n```\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always\n```\nWith an explicit `canary-by-header-value`, the `X-Canary` header must match that exact value to route to the canary backend. So `X-Canary: beta` did **not** match `always`, and all traffic fell through to the stable backend.\n\n(The other `canary-alt` Ingress is a decoy — different host `canary-alt.example.com`, labeled `benchmark.decoy: \"true\"`, and points at `stable-echo`.)\n\n## Fix\nChanged the annotation on `canary-canary` to match the required header value:\n```\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: beta\n```\nNo application Deployments or Services were touched — only the Ingress annotation.\n\n## Verification\n- No header → `stable` ✓\n- `X-Canary: beta` → `canary` ✓ (stable across 3 repeated runs)","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"fbc14d3b-849e-4554-b203-4815fabfe371","total_cost_usd":0.34834899999999996,"usage":{"input_tokens":2634,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19558,"cache_read_input_tokens":181102,"output_tokens":1926,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":19558,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":374,"cache_read_input_tokens":34762,"cache_creation_input_tokens":341,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":341},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":803,"outputTokens":19,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens